# Accessibility Guidelines

## Semantic HTML

Always use semantic HTML elements with proper hierarchy:

```tsx
// ✅ Correct - semantic heading structure
<Typography as="h1" variant="heading" size="4xl">Main Title</Typography>
<Typography as="h2" variant="heading" size="2xl">Section Title</Typography>
<Typography as="h3" variant="subheading" size="xl">Subsection Title</Typography>

// ❌ Avoid - non-semantic elements for headings
<div className="text-4xl font-bold">Main Title</div>
```

## Focus Management

Ensure proper focus states for all interactive elements:

```tsx
// ✅ Correct - proper focus states
<button className="focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-offset-2 focus:ring-ring">
  Click me
</button>

// ✅ Correct - using Button component with built-in focus states
<Button variant="primary">Click me</Button>
```

## Color Contrast

- Use the semantic color system from [src/app/globals.css](mdc:src/app/globals.css)
- Ensure sufficient contrast between text and background
- Test with accessibility tools and screen readers

## Alt Text for Images

Always provide descriptive alt text (max 130 characters):

```tsx
// ✅ Correct - descriptive alt text within limit
<ImageWrapper
  src="/hero-image.jpg"
  alt="Developer using Cursor AI code editor on laptop"
  width={800}
  height={600}
/>

// ❌ Avoid - generic or empty alt text
<ImageWrapper
  src="/hero-image.jpg"
  alt="image"
  width={800}
  height={600}
/>
```

## Keyboard Navigation

- Ensure all interactive elements are keyboard accessible
- Use proper tab order
- Include visible focus indicators
- Support keyboard shortcuts where appropriate

## ARIA Labels

Use ARIA labels for complex interactions:

```tsx
// ✅ Correct - ARIA labels for complex components
<div
  role="button"
  aria-label="Close dialog"
  tabIndex={0}
  onClick={handleClose}
>
  ×
</div>
```

## Screen Reader Support

- Test with screen readers
- Use proper heading hierarchy
- Provide meaningful link text
- Include skip links for navigation